<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>Prescott College awards 4 undergraduate college semester credits for each AP score of 4 or 5 up to a maximum of 20 credits (5 tests). Credit is awarded on a course-by-course basis. AP scores must be sent directly from the College Board/Advanced Placement to the Office of the Registrar. AP awarded credits do not count towards Prescott College's residency requirements.</i>
    <br/>
</p>

